HEADWORD: Ringent
<hw>Rin"gent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ringens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>ringi</ets> to
open wide the mouth: cf. F. <ets>ringent</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Having the lips widely separated and gaping like an open mouth;
<as>as a <ex>ringent</ex> bilabiate corolla</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ringer</ent>⟦br⟧
